    • forEachRemaining

      default void forEachRemaining​(FloatConsumer action)
      Performs the given action for each remaining element until all elements have been processed or the action throws an exception. Actions are performed in the order of iteration, if that order is specified. Exceptions thrown by the action are relayed to the caller.
      Specified by:
      forEachRemaining in interface java.util.PrimitiveIterator<java.lang.Float,​FloatConsumer>
      Parameters:
      action - The action to be performed for each element
      Throws:
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified action is null
      "Implementation Requirements"

      The default implementation behaves as if: 

      
     while (hasNext())
         action.accept(nextFloat());

    • next

      default java.lang.Float next()
      Specified by:
      next in interface java.util.Iterator<java.lang.Float>
      "Implementation Requirements"
      The default implementation boxes the result of calling nextFloat(), and returns that boxed result.

    • forEachRemaining

      default void forEachRemaining​(java.util.function.Consumer<? super java.lang.Float> action)
      Specified by:
      forEachRemaining in interface java.util.Iterator<java.lang.Float>
      "Implementation Requirements"
      If the action is an instance of LongConsumer then it is cast to LongConsumer and passed to forEachRemaining(com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support.function.FloatConsumer); otherwise the action is adapted to an instance of LongConsumer, by boxing the argument of LongConsumer, and then passed to forEachRemaining(com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support.function.FloatConsumer).
